
[1]publicly

   PUB'LICLY, adv. Openly; with exposure to popular view or notice;
   without concealment; as property publicly offered for sale; an opinion
   publicly avowed; a declaration publicly made.

   1. In the name of the community. A reward is publicly offered for the
   discovery of the longitude, or for finding a northwestern passage to
   Asia.
